WEBVTT

00:00:01.710 --> 00:00:04.710
Life in Ur was comfortable.

00:00:04.710 --> 00:00:07.710
We had all the modern conveniences.

00:00:07.710 --> 00:00:11.710
Then Trahova gave us an assignment we never expected.

00:00:11.710 --> 00:00:16.710
One that meant saying goodbye to the life we loved.

00:00:16.710 --> 00:00:21.710
But rather than look behind, Abraham and I looked ahead.

00:00:21.710 --> 00:00:29.710
We had seen Trahova's hand in our lives and we knew he would be with us every step of the journey.

00:00:29.710 --> 00:00:33.710
And he was in ways that surprised us.

00:00:33.710 --> 00:00:36.710
Ways we never could have imagined.

00:00:36.710 --> 00:00:38.710
Trahova did more than help us.

00:00:38.710 --> 00:00:42.710
He fulfilled his every promise.

00:00:42.710 --> 00:00:59.770
Saying goodbye is never easy.

00:00:59.770 --> 00:01:03.770
And even though we were excited about our new LDC assignment,

00:01:03.770 --> 00:01:19.379
it was going to take us further than we'd ever been.

00:01:19.379 --> 00:01:22.379
It wasn't just a new routine.

00:01:22.379 --> 00:01:37.670
It was a holy way of life.

00:01:37.670 --> 00:01:41.670
With each new movement project, we thought about Sarah.

00:01:41.670 --> 00:01:47.459
She focused on the good things ahead.

00:01:47.459 --> 00:01:49.459
And not on what she had left behind.

00:01:49.459 --> 00:01:53.420
And that's what we tried to do.

00:01:53.420 --> 00:03:02.530
Trahova's been so good to us.

00:03:02.530 --> 00:03:06.530
We didn't always know where the next project would take us.

00:03:06.530 --> 00:03:20.979
But we did know that Trahova would be with us every step of the way.

00:03:20.979 --> 00:03:22.979
Jericho was doomed.

00:03:22.979 --> 00:03:24.979
People were scared.

00:03:24.979 --> 00:03:29.979
When the Israelite men showed up at my door, there was barely time to think.

00:03:29.979 --> 00:03:32.979
But I knew what was at stake.

00:03:32.979 --> 00:03:36.979
Even as a young girl, I had heard all the stories.

00:03:36.979 --> 00:03:39.979
Trahova wasn't like the other gods.

00:03:39.979 --> 00:03:45.979
He had dried up the waters of the Red Sea and given his people victory over the Amorites.

00:03:46.979 --> 00:03:53.289
If I helped these men, I knew Jehovah would help me.

00:03:53.289 --> 00:04:00.289
For the first time in my life, I was standing with Jehovah's people on Jehovah's side.

00:04:00.289 --> 00:04:11.939
And my faith was being rewarded.

00:04:11.939 --> 00:04:14.939
There was no doubt about it.

00:04:14.939 --> 00:04:16.939
I had found the truth.

00:04:16.939 --> 00:04:33.620
So, why did I feel so anxious?

00:04:33.620 --> 00:04:47.819
I knew how mom felt about the holidays.

00:04:47.819 --> 00:04:54.939
I also learned how Jehovah felt.

00:04:54.939 --> 00:05:04.430
They displeased him.

00:05:04.430 --> 00:05:06.430
Some changes in my life were easy to make.

00:05:06.430 --> 00:05:20.259
But I really needed Jehovah's help for what I had to do next.

00:05:20.259 --> 00:05:31.319
I loved my mom so much.

00:05:31.319 --> 00:05:34.319
When I explained that I wouldn't celebrate the holidays anymore,

00:05:34.319 --> 00:05:45.509
I could tell that she was hurt.

00:05:45.509 --> 00:05:48.509
But I knew I was doing the right thing.

00:05:48.509 --> 00:05:51.509
And prayed that Jehovah would help her understand.

